{
  "texts": [
    "This sequential approach provides a rational and systematic method for the early identification of colorectal cancer and the benefits of improved classification techniques, DWTs, and CNNs.",
    "This architecture for the proposed framework PolynetDWTCADx incorporates multi-model strength to effectively detect and segment colorectal cancer, since optimum benefits are to be derived from a host of wellestablished approaches.",
    "It relies on CNNs for feature extraction through pre-trained models like ResNet-50, DenseNet-201, and VGG-16.",
    "Each of the CNNs has its unique advantages: ResNet-50 prevents vanishing gradient problems by using residual connections and allows for the development of deeper networks to learn features more effectively; DenseNet-201 enforces feature reuse through the connection between each layer to all subsequent layers, reducing the number of parameters; VGG-16, with convolutional filters much smaller in size, allows for simplicity and a focus on depth, quite effective in smaller medical image datasets.",
    "These CNNs extract hierarchical features that serve as the basis of classification and segmentation tasks."
  ]
}